0the%20ceiling%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingapore-airlines-cabin-crew-burned-by-boiling-water-amid-turbulence-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrew%20member%20was%20burned%20by%20boiling%20water%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20weeks%20later%2C%20at%20an%20industry%20conference%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairlines-to-tighten-seatbelt-rules-use-ai-to-predict-turbulence-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEmirates'%20president%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20incident%20would%20likely%20lead%20to%20stricter%20seatbelt%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncidents%20resulting%20in%20serious%20injuries%20are%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fserious-injuries-due-to-turbulence-are-extremely-rare-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextremely%20rare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20turbulence%20appears%20to%20be%20getting%20more%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20media%20has%20covered%20more%20incidents%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Singapore%20Airlines%20flight.%20But%20they%20are%20also%20becoming%20more%20frequent%20due%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20over%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20according%20to%20Guy%20Gratton%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20aviation%20and%20the%20environment%20at%20Cranfield%20University%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20over%20video%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226501415f-d5e2-4d24-a2a5-a7bcaad06fa9%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20clear%20air%20turbulence%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20know%20that%20there%20is%20wind%2C%20and%20we%20all%20know%20that%20the%20wind%20is%20not%20even.%20It's%20not%20all%20going%20in%20the%20same%20direction%20at%20the%20same%20speed%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Gratton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20when%20you%20get%20a%20difference%20between%20airflow%2C%20you%20get%20friction%20between%20the%20air%20molecules%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20friction%20creates%20a%20more%20complex%20flow%2C%20where%20air%20is%20flowing%20in%20apparently%20random%20directions%20%E2%80%94%20up%2C%20down%2C%20left%2C%20right%2C%20et%20cetera%20%E2%80%94%20and%20changing%20speed.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20turbulence%2C%20and%20it's%20there%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20plane%20flies%20through%20turbulence%2C%20it%20tries%20to%20align%20itself%20with%20the%20changing%20airflow%2C%20so%20its%20motion%20becomes%20erratic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20essentially%20like%20taking%20a%20box%20with%20something%20in%20it%20and%20starting%20to%20shake%20the%20box%20up%20and%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Gratton%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20clearly%2C%20if%20you're%20the%20person%20who's%20inside%20the%20box%2C%20then%20you%20get%20thrown%20around%20inside%20the%20box%2C%20and%20that's%20where%20injuries%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairline-pilot-passengers-should-always-wear-seatbelts-singapore-airlines-turbulence-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPassengers%20are%20told%20to%20keep%20their%20seatbelts%20done%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20if%20you're%20tied%20to%20the%20box%2C%20you're%20much%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20injured%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20altitude%2C%20there%20are%20two%20main%20types%20of%20turbulence.%20One%20is%20caused%20by%20convective%20currents%20and%20is%20associated%20with%20thunderstorms.%20The%20other%20is%20clear%20air%20turbulence%2C%20which%20was%20involved%20in%20the%20Singapore%20Airlines%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20name%20implies%2C%20clear%20air%20turbulence%20is%20hard%20to%20anticipate%20since%20it%20isn't%20associated%20with%20clouds.%20It's%20typically%20found%20at%20the%20edges%20of%20jet%20streams%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0rivers%20of%20fast-flowing%20air.%20Earth%20has%20four%20main%20ones%2C%20two%20near%20the%20poles%20and%20two%20near%20the%20equator.%20The%20difference%20in%20wind%20speed%20between%20these%20jet%20streams%20and%20the%20air%20around%20them%20creates%20clear%20air%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2b53637-9ded-426d-a8a3-cd782d6080fc%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20climate%20crisis%20causes%20more%20turbulence%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1029%2F2023GL103814%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Reading%20found%20that%20turbulence%20was%20getting%20more%20common%20over%20the%20North%20Atlantic.%20It%20said%20that%20over%20a%20typical%20point%2C%20the%20most%20severe%20type%20of%20clear%20air%20turbulence%20increased%20by%2055%25%20between%201979%20and%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20linked%20to%20the%20north%20polar%20jet%20stream.%20Its%20tailwinds%20are%20why%20flying%20from%20the%20US%20to%20Europe%20is%20faster%20than%20flying%20from%20Europe%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGratton%20explained%20how%20the%20warming%20atmosphere%20speeds%20up%20the%20jet%20streams%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0causing%20more%20severe%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20linked%20to%20the%20relationship%20between%20two%20layers%20of%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%20The%20lowest%20one%20is%20the%20troposphere%2C%20where%20the%20temperature%20cools%20as%20you%20get%20higher.%20Above%20that%20is%20the%20stratosphere%2C%20where%20the%20temperature%20is%20constant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20happening%20with%20climate%20change%20is%20the%20troposphere%20is%20getting%20warmer%2C%20the%20lower%20stratosphere%20is%20actually%20getting%20slightly%20colder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20increasing%20difference%20in%20energy%20between%20the%20two%20layers%20means%20more%20energy%20goes%20into%20the%20jet%20stream%2C%20Gratton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20enlarges%20Rossby%20waves%2C%20which%20are%20meanders%20found%20in%20the%20jet%20stream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20if%20you're%20trying%20to%20fly%20across%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20you've%20now%20got%20bigger%20waves%20in%20the%20jet%20stream%2C%20and%20you've%20also%20got%20more%20energy%20in%20the%20jet%20stream%2C%26quot%3B%20Gratton%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20that%20is%20creating%20more%20friction%2C%20which%20is%20creating%20more%20turbulence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTherefore%20crossing%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20making%20encounters%20with%20clear%20air%20turbulence%20more%20likely%20and%20more%20severe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturbulence-more-frequent-stronger-expert-aviation-explains-why-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720002842000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664dbd799fc063e829b38849%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturbulence-more-frequent-stronger-expert-aviation-explains-why-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BClimate%20change%20is%20making%20encounters%20with%20clear%20air%20turbulence%20more%20likely%20and%20more%20severe%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20University%20of%20Cranfield's%20Guy%20Gratton%20told%20BI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40businessinsider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturbulence-more-frequent-stronger-expert-aviation-explains-why-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sandra%20Yi%20Sencindiver%20Talks%20Hopes%20for%20%E2%80%98Geek%20Girl%E2%80%99%20Season%202%2C%20Teases%20Secretive%20%E2%80%98Alien%E2%80%99%20Series%3A%20%E2%80%98Fans%20of%20the%20Original%20Movies%E2%80%99%20Will%20Be%20%E2%80%98Very%20Pleased%E2%80%99%22%2C%22con