%2C%20said%20Mike%20Moffatt%2C%20a%20senior%20director%20at%20the%20Smart%20Prosperity%20Institute%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Ottawa.%20That%20public%20sentiment%20pushed%20officials%20in%20Ottawa%20to%20warm%20to%20a%20more%20hands-on%20approach.%20%26quot%3BCanadians%20just%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20home%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't%20really%20care%20about%20the%20intricacies%20of%20constitutional%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Moffat%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20last%20year%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20launched%20an%20initiative%20%E2%80%94%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fliberal.ca%2Four-platform%2F1-4-million-new-homes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHousing%20Accelerator%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20that%20incentivizes%20local%20governments%20to%20legalize%20denser%20housing%20construction%2C%20including%20by%20mass%20transit%2C%20and%20otherwise%20stimulate%20more%20home%20building.%20In%20exchange%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20and%20his%20Liberal%20party%20have%20opened%20up%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20infrastructure%20funding%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0from%20water%20to%20transit%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20support%20that%20new%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20pushes%20provinces%20and%20cities%20to%20create%20more%20pro-housing%20policies%2C%20including%20ending%20single-family%20zoning%2C%20loosening%20restrictions%20on%20how%20tall%20and%20close%20together%20residential%20buildings%20can%20be%2C%20opening%20up%20government%20land%20for%20housing%2C%20and%20eliminating%20parking%20mandates.%20The%20federal%20government%20first%20made%20deals%20directly%20with%20all%20of%20the%20country's%20major%20cities%2C%20which%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Ffederal-government-fraser-housing-strategy-1.7171889%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20allow%20750%2C000%20more%20homes%20to%20be%20permitted%20than%20otherwise%20would%20have%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20Trudeau%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fjustin-trudeau-budget-housing-1.7161005%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20an%20additional%20%245%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20infrastructure%20grants%20for%20provinces%20and%20territories%20that%20implement%20pro-housing%20policies%2C%20including%20legalizing%20%26quot%3Bmissing%20middle%26quot%3B%20homes%2C%20which%20includes%20medium-density%20housing%20like%20duplexes%2C%20triplexes%2C%20and%20small%20apartment%20buildings.%20The%20most%20recent%20push%20is%20part%20of%20Trudeau's%20larger%20housing%20plan%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20get%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftoronto.citynews.ca%2F2024%2F04%2F12%2Ftrudeau-reveals-liberal-plan-to-build-3-9m-homes-by-2031-amid-housing-crisis%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3.9%20million%20new%20homes%20built%20by%202031.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20federal%20push%20has%20already%20been%20quite%20successful%20in%20changing%20the%20housing%20policy%20landscape%20across%20the%20country%2C%20Moffat%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20their%20deals%20with%20the%20government%2C%20all%20of%20the%20major%20cities%20now%20allow%20at%20least%20four%20units%20to%20be%20built%20on%20single-family%20lots.%20Certain%20provinces%2C%20like%20British%20Columbia%2C%20have%20been%20much%20more%20willing%20to%20push%20pro-housing%20policies.%20Local%20governments%20in%20places%20like%20Ontario%20and%20Alberta%20have%20put%20up%20more%20of%20a%20fight.%20However%2C%20the%20approach%20creates%20some%20political%20cover%20for%20policymakers%20facing%20anti-housing%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUptake%20hasn't%20been%20universal%2C%20but%20overall%20it's%20been%20quite%20strong%2C%26quot%3B%20Moffat%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20seen%20some%20municipal%20changes%20that%2C%20even%2020%20months%20ago%2C%20I%20would%20have%20said%20were%20highly%2C%20highly%20unlikely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20denser%20housing%20is%20legal%20doesn't%20mean%20it%20will%20get%20built.%20Building%20missing%20middle%20housing%20and%20other%20more%20affordable%20homes%20needs%20to%20be%20attractive%20to%20developers.%20And%20with%20home%20construction%20costs%20way%20up%2C%20that's%20a%20steeper%20ask%2C%20said%20Matti%20Siemiatycki%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20Infrastructure%20Institute%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto's%20School%20of%20Cities.%20%26quot%3BWith%20the%20rising%20interest%20rates%20with%20rising%20construction%20costs%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20product%20that%20used%20to%20be%20finance%20is%20now%20becoming%20much%20harder%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECity%20governments%20have%20long%20been%20%26quot%3Bbiased%20towards%20homeowners%20and%20not%20towards%20renters%2C%26quot%3B%20Mosche%20Lander%2C%20a%20Concordia%20University%20economist%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-housing-crisis-bubble-imploding-real-estate-prices-rent-decline-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20BI%20late%20last%20year%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20support%20policies%20that%20limit%20homebuilding%20and%20keep%20home%20values%20elevated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20housing%20affordability%20crisis%20in%20Canada%20is%20driven%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20housing%20and%20rising%20demand.%20Over%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F03%2F22%2Famericas%2Fcanada-record-population-growth-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflux%20of%20new%20immigrants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rampant%20investor%20speculation%2C%20and%20rapidly%20rising%20construction%20costs%20have%20also%20sent%20prices%20up.%20The%20average%20home%20value%20in%20Canada%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-65688460%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20than%20doubled%20since%202011%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Rents%20are%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cp24.com%2Fnews%2Faverage-asking-rent-prices-reach-2-193-in-february-up-10-5-from-2023-1.6802734%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2020%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20And%20a%20ballooning%20number%20of%20Canadians%20are%20spending%20more%20than%20they%20can%20afford%20on%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20most%20of%20Canada's%20housing%20landscape%20looks%20like%20California's%20supply-starved%20and%20deeply%20unaffordable%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20difference%20is%20that%20California%20makes%20up%20about%2012%20or%2013%25%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20whereas%20Ontario%20and%20BC%20combined%20are%20over%20half%2C%26quot%3B%20Moffat%20said.%20%26quot%3BHalf%20to%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20country%20is%20unaffordable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiemiatycki%20said%20there's%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Bsubtle%20but%20noticeable%20change%26quot%3B%20in%20how%20Canadians%20view%20residential%20density.%20Many%20homeowners%20who%20previously%20opposed%20densification%20are%20starting%20to%20realize%2C%20%26quot%3Beven%20if%20it's%20not%20them%20that%20rising%20prices%20and%20skyrocketing%20impact%2C%20it%20might%20be%20their%20children%2C%20or%20their%20colleagues%2C%20or%20their%20elders%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPro-housing%20policies%20are%20increasingly%20popular%20across%20Canada's%20ideological%20spectrum.%20The%20federal%20opposition%20leader%2C%20Pierre%20Poilievre%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%2C%20argues%20Trudeau's%20government%20hasn't%20gone%20far%20enough%20and%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fpoilievre-housing-plan-1.6966907%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposed%20his%20own%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20require%20cities%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20new%20homes%20built%20by%2015%25%20each%20year%20or%20lose%20out%20on%20federal%20grant%20money.%20It%20would%20also%20impose%20a%20fine%20on%20cities%20that%20tolerate%20%26quot%3BNIMBY%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20anti-development%20%26quot%3BNot%20in%20My%20Backyard%26quot%3B%20philosophy%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0opposition%20to%20housing%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%202021%20Infrastructure%20Investment%20and%20Jobs%20Act%2C%20the%20US%20federal%20government%20is%20providing%20states%20and%20cities%20across%20the%20country%20with%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20funding%20for%20transportation%20and%20other%20infrastructure%20projects.%20Some%20American%20fans%20of%20Canada's%20Housing%20Accelerator%20Fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fyfreemark%2Fstatus%2F1800921956268880362%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuggest%20it%20could%20be%20a%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20US%20efforts%20to%20incentivize%20denser%20and%20more%20abundant%20housing%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-housing-crisis-prices-rents-real-estate-infrastructure-funding-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720000683000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667f18c640cf2af6e4f6e6bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-housing-crisis-prices-rents-real-estate-infrastructure-funding-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Canadian%20federal%20government%20is%20finding%20new%20ways%20to%20pressure%20local%20governments%20to%20legalize%20denser%20housing%20to%20solve%20the%20country's%20home%20shortage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-housing-crisis-prices-rents-real-estate-infrastructure-funding-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%2