%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-homebuying-soaring-lumber-prices-new-homes-construction-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elumber%20mania%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20lumber%20prices%20soared%20to%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20all%20were%20cooped%20up%20in%20our%20homes%2C%20many%20people%20looked%20around%2C%20realized%20they%20hated%20their%20abodes%2C%20and%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20make%20a%20(sometimes%20drastic)%20change.%20This%20meant%20a%20lot%20of%20moves%2C%20even%20more%20makeover%20projects%2C%20and%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20lumber.%20Unfortunately%20for%20the%20motivated%20remodelers%2C%20the%20supply%20side%20of%20the%20equation%20was%20caught%20flat-footed%3A%20Sawmill%20operators%20had%20scaled%20back%20operations%20under%20the%20assumption%20the%20pandemic%20would%20mean%20%3Cem%3Eless%20%3C%2Fem%3Eactivity%2C%20not%20more.%20The%20price%20of%20Western%20SPF%20two-by-four%20lumber%20%E2%80%94%20an%20industry%20benchmark%20%E2%80%94%20shot%20up%20from%20under%20%24400%20per%20thousand%20board%20feet%20in%20January%202020%20to%20over%20%241%2C600%20in%20May%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20comes%20up%20often%20comes%20down%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Flumber-prices-plunge-home-building-season-demand-falls-flat-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elumber%20prices%20came%20down%20hard%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20demand%20decelerated%20and%20supply%20ramped%20up%20to%20a%20speed%20that's%20no%20longer%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20low%20and%20slow%2C%20and%20it's%20kind%20of%20been%20that%20way%20for%20a%20while%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stinson%20Dean%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Deacon%20Lumber%2C%20a%20lumber%20trading%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20peaking%20in%20spring%202021%2C%20lumber%20prices%20briefly%20collapsed%20before%20jumping%20back%20up%20to%20%241%2C400%20in%20early%202022.%20Later%20that%20year%2C%20prices%20nose-dived%20to%20the%20%24300-to-%24400%20range%2C%20and%20they've%20stuck%20there.%20While%20these%20prices%20are%20similar%20to%20the%20pre-2020%20levels%2C%20Dustin%20Jalbert%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20on%20wood%20products%20at%20Fastmarkets%20RISI%2C%20told%20me%20that%20changes%20to%20the%20industry%20and%20the%20higher%20cost%20of%20production%20meant%20lumber%20suppliers%20were%20getting%20squeezed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20large%20part%20of%20the%20industry%20is%20losing%20money%20at%20these%20prices%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Jalbert%20said.%20He%20joked%20that%20lumber%20was%20having%20another%20%26quot%3Bmoment%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20media%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20for%20the%20opposite%20reasons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupply%20and%20demand%20were%20the%20culprits%20when%20prices%20were%20soaring%2C%20and%20they've%20helped%20fuel%20the%20tumble%2C%20too.%20Let's%20start%20with%20the%20demand%20side%3A%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20jacked%20up%20its%20key%20interest%20rate%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20bringing%20mortgage%20rates%20along%20for%20the%20ride.%20The%20average%2030-year%20mortgage%20rate%20was%20under%203%25%20just%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20but%20now%20sits%20at%20about%207%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20interest%20rates%20mean%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Finterestrates%2Fu-s-housing-starts-unexpectedly-tumble-5-5-in-may-1033492820%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20housing%20is%20being%20built%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20existing-home%20sales%20are%20down%20to%20levels%20not%20seen%20since%20the%20Great%20Recession.%20If%20you%20own%20a%20home%20and%20are%20looking%20to%20move%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20doubling%20your%20mortgage%20rate%20is%20a%20tough%20pill%20to%20swallow%2C%20leading%20people%20to%20stay%20put.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemodels%20and%20repairs%20have%20also%20slowed%20down.%20A%20lot%20of%20activity%20was%20pulled%20forward%20during%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20new%20deck%20or%20an%20addition%20already%20did%20so%20in%202020%20and%202021.%20Even%20if%20people%20%3Cem%3Edo%3C%2Fem%3E%20have%20projects%20they'd%20like%20to%20undertake%20in%20their%20homes%2C%20they're%20not%20really%20jazzed%20about%20tapping%20into%20their%20home%20equity%20to%20do%20it%2C%20given%20interest%20rates.%20Homeowners%20also%20tend%20to%20do%20the%20most%20work%20on%20their%20houses%20within%20a%20few%20years%20of%20buying%20them%2C%20so%20if%20they're%20not%20moving%2C%20they're%20not%20renovating%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Jannke%2C%20a%20principal%20at%20Forest%20Economic%20Advisors%2C%20said%20this%20housing-market%20malaise%20is%20a%20big%20problem%20for%20the%20lumber%20industry.%20He%20said%20residential%20construction%20%E2%80%94%20including%20new%20builds%2C%20renovations%2C%20and%20repairs%20%E2%80%94%20makes%20up%2070%25%20to%2075%25%20of%20actual%20lumber%20consumption.%20Housing%20starts%20are%20down%2018%25%20from%20where%20they%20were%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202022%20to%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20and%20spending%20on%20residential%20improvements%20are%20off%20by%2021%25%2C%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%2C%20he%20said.%20Given%20the%20weakness%20there%2C%20you%20get%20the%20demand%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20supply%20end%2C%20the%20long%20and%20short%20of%20it%20is%20that%20producers%20got%20a%20bit%20out%20over%20their%20(wooden)%20skis.%20The%20amount%20of%20lumber%20being%20produced%20might%20have%20been%20nice%20in%202021%2C%20but%20not%20so%20much%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20pandemic-era%20high%20prices%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20investing%20in%20sawmills%20(aka%20the%20place%20where%20a%20tree%20goes%20to%20become%20a%20stick%20of%20lumber)%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20southern%20US.%20Some%20have%20closed%2C%20but%20on%20net%2C%20US%20sawmills%20are%20producing%20about%204%20billion%20more%20board%20feet%20than%20they%20were%20in%202022%2C%20Jannke%20said.%20It's%20not%20just%20an%20American%20problem%3A%20Suppliers%20in%20British%20Columbia%20have%20historically%20exported%20a%20lot%20of%20wood%20to%20China%2C%20but%20the%20Chinese%20property%20market%20has%20collapsed%2C%20so%20that%20lumber%20isn't%20being%20shipped%20overseas%20and%20instead%20is%20being%20diverted%20into%20the%20already%20swamped%20US%20market.%20Tariffs%20on%20lumber%20coming%20from%20Canada%20into%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nahb.org%2Fblog%2F2024%2F02%2Flumber-tariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20expected%20to%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20summer%2C%20so%20Canadian%20mills%20are%20keeping%20maintaining%20production%20before%20that%20happens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20so%20much%20wood%2C%26quot%3B%20Jannke%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20this%20is%20a%20classic%20bullwhip%20effect%2C%20a%20phenomenon%20where%20changes%20in%20consumer%20demand%20cause%20outsize%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20supply%20chain.%20It's%20also%20classic%20greed%20%E2%80%94%20people%20saw%20lumber's%20eye-popping%20prices%20in%202021%20and%202022%20and%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20get%20in%20on%20the%20production%20game%20or%20build%20out%20existing%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20got%20optimistic%2C%26quot%3B%20Jalbert%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20to%20think%20about%20is%20the%20lead%20time%20to%20start%20up%20a%20sawmill.%20It%20takes%20two%20to%20three%20years%20to%20ramp%20up%20that%20supply%20%E2%80%94%20let's%20call%20it%2018%20to%2024%20months%20from%20breaking%20ground%20on%20the%20project%20to%20when%20it%20is%20fully%20ramped%20up%20to%20full%20capacity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20that%20new%20production%20capacity%20became%20operational%20right%20as%20things%20started%20to%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20investment%20in%20new%20supply%20that%20was%20planned%20before%20COVID%2C%20and%20then%20that%20was%20supercharged%20during%20COVID%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20said.%20Some%20of%20those%20projects%20were%20paid%20for%20with%20cash%2C%20but%20others%20were%20financed%20with%20debt%2C%20and%20sawmills%20are%20still%20pumping%20out%20supply%20in%20order%20to%20pay%20those%20debts.%20Instead%20of%20scaling%20back%20and%20waiting%20for%20prices%20to%20bounce%20back%2C%20they're%20stuck%20producing%20lumber%20for%20a%20market%20that%20doesn't%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20cash-flow%20stresses%2C%20they've%20got%20the%20debt%20to%20service%2C%20and%20they've%20just%20got%20this%20brand-new%20facility%2C%20so%20they%20can't%20really%20afford%20to%20not%20have%20any%20kind%20of%20cash%20flow%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey'd%20rather%20lose%20money%20and%20run%20their%20new%20facility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20path%20to%20higher%20prices%20likely%20runs%20through%20sawmill%20closures%2C%20but%20many%20in%20the%20industry%20aren't%20ready%20to%20pack%20it%20in.%20Some%20mill%20operators%20feel%20like%20they've%20done%20their%20fair%20share%20to%20slow%20operations%20and%20now%20it's%20someone%20else's%20turn.%20It's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprisoners-dilemma-in-real-life-2013-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprisoner's%20dilemma%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20for%20wood.%20Many%20lumber%20producers%2C%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20came%20into%20the%20year%20expecting%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates%20sooner%2C%20triggering%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20demand.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-2024-outlook-us-economy-fed-cuts-powell-jobs-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThat%20hasn't%20happened%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mill%20operators%20also%20remember%20the%20experience%20of%20not%20having%20enough%20supply%20to%20meet%20a%20spike%20in%20demand%2C%20and%20they%20know%20that%20ramping%20back%20up%20takes%20time%2C%20so%20they%20may%20be%20hesitating%20to%20ramp%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20term%2C%20there's%20room%20for%20optimism.%20The%20US%20needs%20to%20build%20more%20housing%2C%20so%20the%20long-run%20fundamentals%20look%20good%2C%20and%20interest%20rates%20are%20likely%20to%20come%20down%20eventually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLower%20interest%20rates%20fixes%20this%20thing%20in%20a%20hurry%2C%20because%20demand%20can%20come%20back%20pretty%20quick%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20said.%20He%20told%20me%20that%20for%20the%20moment%20he's%20taking%20it%20easy%2C%20%26quot%3Bposting%20a%20lot%20of%20fishing%20pictures%20and%20waiting%20for%20the%20market%20to%20figure%20itself%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20getting%20ready%20to%20work%20a%20lot%20harder%20once%20things%20get%20moving%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20those%20in%20the%20lumber%20industry%20may%20not%20be%20having%20a%20fantastic%20time%2C%20if%20you're%20in%20the%20market%20for%20lumber%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20time%20to%20buy.%20Dean%20said%20that%20if%20lower%20prices%20haven't%20filtered%20down%20to%20stores%20yet%2C%20he%20expects%20them%20to%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20been%20putting%20off%20a%20remodel%20for%20three%20years%2C%20a%20deck%2C%20a%20fence%2C%20right%20now%20%E2%80%94%20and%20you%20need%20to%20be%20watching%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20this%20summer%20will%20be%20the%20best%20time%20to%20secure%20materials%20for%20that%20in%20four-plus%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20really%20want%20to%20get%20into%20the%20weeds%20on%20this%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20suppose%20if%20you're%20considering%20a%20big%20project%20you%20do%20%E2%80%94%20there%20is%20some%20wonkiness.%20While%20framing-lumber%20prices%20have%20come%20down%2C%20the%20costs%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20building%20materials%20haven't.%20If%20you're%20building%20a%20deck%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20deck%20planks%20won't%20be%20cheap%2C%20though%20the%20framing%20will%20be.%20Building%20a%20house%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20more%20expensive%20than%20it%20was%20in%202020.%20Robert%20Dietz%2C%20a%20senior%20vice%20president%20and%20chief%20economist%20at%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Home%20Builders%2C%20said%20the%20costs%20of%20residential%20construction%20materials%20were%20up%20by%20more%20than%2046%25%20since%20May%20of%20that%20year.%20They've%20been%20roughly%20flat%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20lumber%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOther%20prices%20remain%20elevated%20for%20material%20costs%2C%20meaning%20home%20prices%20will%20remain%20elevated%2C%26quot%3B%20Dietz%20said.%20The%20silver%20lining%20here%20is%20that%20building%20a%20new%20house%20isn't%20%3Cem%3Eas%20%3C%2Fem%3Eexpensive%20as%20it%20could%20be%20if%20lumber%20hadn't%20come%20down%20%E2%80%94%20lumber's%20decline%20has%20helped%20prices%20stay%20relatively%20stable%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJannke%20said%20that%20while%20the%20lower%20lumber%20prices%20hadn't%20resulted%20in%20lower%20housing%20costs%2C%20%26quot%3Bhomebuilder%20margins%20are%20at%20or%20near%20record%20levels.%26quot%3B%20If%20you're%20paying%20a%20contractor%20for%20your%20project%2C%20they%20may%20not%20be%20too%20keen%20to%20pass%20the%20price%20savings%20on%20to%20you.%20They're%20paying%20for%20other%20factors%20like%20labor%2C%20maybe%20wiring%20and%20sheeting.%20They%20also%20are%20running%20a%20business%20where%20they'd%20like%20to%20make%20as%20much%20money%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20quoting%20the%20job%20lower%20because%20the%20dimensional-lumber%20price%20is%20lower%2C%26quot%3B%20Jalbert%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20quote%20a%20job%20because%20they%20look%20at%20what%20people's%20income%20is%20at%20and%20they%20look%20at%20what%20home%20prices%20are%20at%20and%20they%20say%2C%20no%2C%20this%20is%20the%20price%20for%20that%20job%2C%20regardless%20of%20what%20the%20inputs%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20have%20to%20accept%20the%20quote%20with%20no%20questions%20asked.%20You%20can%20try%20to%20negotiate%20%E2%80%94%20hey%2C%20maybe%20even%20show%20them%20this%20article%20and%20argue%20that%20things%20should%20be%20getting%20cheaper%20for%20them.%20Or%2C%20if%20you%20dare%2C%20you%20can%20always%20buy%20wholesale%20and%20try%20to%20do%20it%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flumber-wood-prices-americas-economic-future-real-estate-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720000442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668415441f0c1cd6d730a686%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flumber-wood-prices-americas-economic-future-real-estate-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20see-saw%20prices%20for%20wood%20tell%20us%20about%20America's%20economic%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flumber-wood-prices-americas-economic-future-real-estate-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Revered%20screenwriter%20Robert%20Towne%20dies%20aged%2089%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720000388000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F9218%2Flive%2F206f9380-391e-11ef-bdc5-41d7421c2adf.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc3g3dy6jdlpo%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Oscar-winning%20writer%20penned%20the%20scripts%20for%20f