w%20what%20any%20of%20that%20was%20like%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flifeguard-labor-shortage-pools-cutting-opening-hours-closing-work-jobs-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifeguard%20is%20now%20on%20life%20support%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20American%20Lifeguard%20Association%20reported%20last%20year%20that%20one-third%20of%20the%20country's%20309%2C000%20public%20swimming%20pools%20would%20either%20close%20for%20the%20summer%20season%20or%20operate%20in%20a%20limited%20capacity%2C%20marking%20the%20third%20year%20in%20a%20row%20for%20dramatically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhire-lifeguards-ymca-pools-florida-staff-shortage-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduced%20pool%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%20nationwide.%20My%20childhood%20pool%20%E2%80%94%20where%20my%20grandfather%20worked%20as%20a%20locker-room%20attendant%20in%20the%201940s%20and%20my%20dad%20learned%20to%20swim%20in%20the%201960s%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20closed%20to%20the%20public%20since%202020.%20Public%20beaches%20share%20the%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20predicament%20continues.%20Some%20cities%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flifeguard-shortage-large-signing-bonus-job-retention-hourly-pay-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturned%20to%20creative%20measures%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20recruiting%20and%20training%20retirees%20for%20seasonal%20positions%20or%20lowering%20age%20requirements%20for%20certification.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20it%20hasn't%20been%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20an%20emblem%20of%20summer%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20object%20of%20poolside%20fawning%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamptons-lifeguard-luxury-homes-pool-parties-job-diary-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20American%20lifeguard%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20somehow%20become%20an%20endangered%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20lifeguard%20crisis%20isn't%20entirely%20unprecedented%3A%20Intermittent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fhealth%2Farchive%2F2023%2F06%2Flifeguard-shortage-pools-history%2F674340%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshortages%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20befallen%20the%20nation's%20pools%20and%20beaches%20since%20at%20least%20the%20'20s.%20But%20my%20peak%20pool%20patronage%20took%20place%20in%20the%20late%20'90s%2C%20which%20happened%20to%20coincide%20with%20an%20unusually%20long%20stretch%20of%20high%20lifeguard%20recruitment%20and%20retention.%20And%20somehow%20this%20was%20happening%20at%20a%20time%20when%20many%20US%20cities%20were%20prioritizing%20public%20spending%20on%20law%20enforcement%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2020%2F06%2F12%2Fupshot%2Fcities-grew-safer-police-budgets-kept-growing.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpense%20of%3C%2Fa%3E%20other%20public%20services%2C%20including%20recreational%20amenities%20such%20as%20parks%20and%20pools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20brought%20on%20this%20age%20of%20lifeguard%20plenty%3F%20Cue%20the%20opening%20montage%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-who-were-on-baywatch-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBaywatch%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222583%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Girls%20Of%20%26quot%3BBaywatch%26quot%3B%20in%20red%20swimsuits%20holding%20a%20surfboard.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667ebe9350b021b5caea48ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20hit%20'90s%20TV%20show%20made%20lifeguarding%20seem%20like%20a%20dream%20job.%20%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20popular%20syndicated%20TV%20series%2C%20which%20centered%20on%20a%20crew%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaywatch-cast-actors-then-and-now-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpossibly%20good-looking%20Southern%20California%20lifeguards%3C%2Fa%3E%20saving%20lives%20and%20breaking%20hearts%20in%20high-cut%2C%20tomato-red%20swimsuits%2C%20aired%20from%201989%20to%202001.%20%26quot%3BIt%20showed%20lifeguarding%20as%20a%20glamorous%20lifestyle%20and%20made%20it%20look%20like%20a%20great%20profession%2C%26quot%3B%20Wyatt%20Werneth%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20American%20Lifeguard%20Association%2C%20said.%20Werneth%20became%20a%20professional%20lifeguard%20in%20the%20early%20'90s%20%E2%80%94%20aka%20peak%20%26quot%3BBaywatch%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20told%20me%20that%20the%20show%20had%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20the%20public's%20perception%20of%20his%20industry%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20prestigious.%20You%20wore%20your%20lifeguard%20uniform%20with%20pride.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%20who%20lifeguarded%20in%20their%20teens%20and%2020s%20remembered%20it%20fondly.%20%26quot%3BI%20enjoyed%20lifeguarding%20because%20it%20was%20what%20I%20considered%20a%20'professional%20job%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Jessi%20Adler%2C%20who%20lifeguarded%20at%20various%20pools%20throughout%20her%20high-school%20and%20college%20years%20in%20Michigan%20between%201995%20and%202003.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20many%20of%20my%20friends%20were%20working%20at%20a%20fast-food%20joint%2C%20I%20had%20learned%20a%20real%20skill%20and%20was%20responsible%20for%20people's%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20a%20public-relations%20director%20in%20Central%20Texas%2C%20Adler%20and%20her%20husband%20were%20recently%20volunteering%20as%20tour%20guides%20and%20maintenance%20workers%20at%20Lyndon%20B.%20Johnson%20State%20Park%20when%20park%20officials%20offered%20to%20pay%20for%20her%20lifeguard%20recertification%20so%20she%20could%20pitch%20in%20with%20an%20occasional%20pool%20shift.%20The%20request%20was%20deferred%20because%20of%20pool%20renovations%2C%20but%20the%20need%20hasn't%20gone%20away%3A%20The%20park%20issued%20a%20plea%20for%20lifeguard%20applicants%20on%20its%20community%20Facebook%20page%20in%20early%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scenario%20presents%20a%20sharp%20departure%20from%20Adler's%20youth%2C%20when%20lifeguarding%20seemed%20like%20the%20ultimate%20summer%20job.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20being%20so%20excited%20when%20I%20was%20old%20enough%20to%20be%20eligible%20to%20take%20the%20certification%20test%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20lifeguards%20in%20the%20US%20are%20under%20the%20age%20of%2025.%20Jason%20Russell%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20history%20and%20labor%20studies%20at%20SUNY%20Empire%20State%2C%20told%20me%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20lifeguarding%20as%20a%20young%20person's%20job%20keeps%20it%20from%20becoming%20professionalized%20%E2%80%94%20which%20makes%20it%20more%20prone%20to%20ebbs%20and%20flows.%20Instead%20of%20a%20career%20with%20long-term%20advancement%20opportunities%20that's%20compensated%20accordingly%2C%20it's%20seen%20as%20entry-level%20service%20work%20for%20kids.%20This%20poses%20a%20variety%20of%20staffing%20challenges.%20In%20beach-resort%20communities%2C%20for%20example%2C%20there's%20often%20a%20lack%20of%20nearby%20housing%20available%20to%20low-wage%20seasonal%20workers%20who%20may%20or%20may%20not%20have%20the%20means%20of%20getting%20to%20work%20from%20more-affordable%20accommodations%20further%20afield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20'Baywatch%2C'%20they%20never%20had%20any%20problems%20finding%20places%20to%20live%2C%26quot%3B%20Russell%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20driving%20around%20in%20cars.%20The%20material%20circumstances%20of%20their%20lives%20were%20much%20different%20than%20the%20average%20actual%20lifeguard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20glossy%20portrayal%20of%20the%20job%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BBaywatch%26quot%3B%20effect%20could%20only%20last%20so%20long.%20By%20the%202010s%2C%20lifeguard%20shortages%20had%20resurfaced%20as%20a%20widespread%20concern.%20When%20the%20pandemic%20came%20along%2C%20the%20predicament%20ratcheted%20up%20to%20a%20full-blown%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWerneth%20told%20me%20that%20when%20pools%20shut%20down%20in%202020%2C%20prospective%20lifeguarding%20recruits%20missed%20out%20on%20training%20and%20certification%20opportunities%20and%20found%20work%20elsewhere.%20Others%20say%20the%20shortages%20stem%20from%20an%20increased%20demand%20for%20lifeguards%20at%20commercial%20aquatic%20facilities%20%E2%80%94%20waterparks%20have%20grown%20by%20nearly%2050%25%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20since%202014%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Waterpark%20Association%2C%20a%20global%20trade%20group.%20But%20those%20explanations%20ignore%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwater-swim-safety-tips-prevent-drowning-parents-kids-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmericans%20simply%20can't%20swim%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Red%20Cross%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Americans%20either%20can't%20swim%20at%20all%20or%20lack%20the%20basic%20water%20skills%20to%20swim%20safely.%20That's%20a%20startling%20plummet%20from%20the%2093%25%20of%20men%20and%2074%25%20of%20women%20who%20said%20they%20knew%20how%20to%20swim%20in%20a%201991%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fajph.aphapublications.org%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.2105%2FAJPH.86.1.93%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20the%20American%20Journal%20of%20Public%20Health.%20Fewer%20swimmers%20means%20fewer%20prospective%20lifeguards.%20And%20this%20problem%20feeds%20on%20itself%3A%20A%20lot%20of%20Americans%20can't%20swim%20because%20of%20poor%20access%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marketplace.org%2F2023%2F09%2F18%2Fpublic-swimming-pools-by-the-numbers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20swimming%20facilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20lessons%2C%20and%20those%20training%20opportunities%20get%20harder%20to%20find%20thanks%20to%20the%20shortage%20of%20qualified%20lifeguards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crisis%20is%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20our%20nation's%20past%20when%20swimming%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20beloved%20pastime.%20In%20his%202007%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BContested%20Waters%3A%20A%20Social%20History%20of%20Swimming%20Pools%20in%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeff%20Wiltse%20cited%20a%201933%20survey%20that%20found%20that%20many%20Americans%20prized%20swimming%20in%20public%20pools%20as%20much%20as%20going%20to%20the%20movies.%20%26quot%3BPools%20became%20emblems%20of%20a%20new%2C%20distinctly%20modern%20version%20of%20the%20good%20life%20that%20valued%20leisure%2C%20pleasure%2C%20and%20beauty%2C%26quot%3B%20Wiltse%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%2C%20in%20short%2C%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20life%20Americans%20wanted%20to%20live.%26quot%3B%20Between%201933%20and%201938%2C%20some%20750%20public%20pools%20were%20constructed%20under%20the%20New%20Deal.%20The%20art-deco%20splendor%20of%20some%20surviving%20pools%20of%20this%20era%20such%20as%20the%20grand%20Astoria%20Park%20pool%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20serve%20as%20poignant%20reminders%20of%20this%20public-swimming%20heyday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Astoria%20Park%20swimming%20pool%20in%20New%20York%20City%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667ebd4340cf2af6e4f69017%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Astoria%20Park%20pool%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20surviving%20reminders%20of%20America's%20aquatic%20glory%20days.%3Cp%3EKENA%20BETANCUR%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20romance%20did%20not%20last.%20As%20white%20Americans%20moved%20to%20the%20suburbs%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabandoned-swimming-pools-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20pools%20began%20their%20long%20and%20steady%20decline%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Movement%2C%20many%20cities%20opted%20to%20close%20public%20swimming%20facilities%20instead%20of%20complying%20with%20desegregation%20mandates%2C%20which%20sharply%20reduced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-shares-how-hard-sign-up-kids-for-swim-lessons-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccess%20to%20swimming%20lessons%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Suburbanites%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20preferred%20the%20privacy%20of%20backyard%20pools%20and%20private%20clubs.%20By%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20a%20person's%20race%2C%20socioeconomic%20status%2C%20and%20whether%20they%20lived%20in%20a%20city%20or%20suburb%20became%20key%20predictors%20of%20their%20ability%20to%20swim.%20That%20pattern%20persists%20to%20this%20day%2C%20narrowing%20the%20pool%20of%20prospective%20lifeguards%20to%20draw%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20swim%20disparities%20also%20influenced%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flifeguards-reveal-worst-experiences-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escope%20of%20a%20lifeguard's%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20younger%20brother%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20lifeguard%20at%20several%20Milwaukee%20city%20pools%20in%20the%20late%202000s%20and%20early%202010s%2C%20recalled%20having%20to%20make%20numerous%20rescues%20at%20one%20particularly%20high-traffic%20pool%20and%20waterpark.%20Adler%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20recounted%20her%20rescues%20in%20suburban%20Michigan%20as%20%26quot%3Bvery%20minimal%20and%20never%20serious.%26quot%3B%20(Though%20she%20did%20notice%20that%20people's%20swimming%20skills%20were%20more%20of%20a%20mixed%20bag%20at%20her%20college%20pool%2C%20where%20patrons%20came%20from%20a%20variety%20of%20backgrounds%2C%20than%20at%20her%20community's%20country%20club%20and%20high%20school.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20problem%2C%20period%2C%20with%20a%20decline%20in%20swimming%20lessons%2C%26quot%3B%20Russell%2C%20the%20labor%20historian%2C%20told%20me%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20inability%20to%20swim%20was%20more%20pronounced%20in%20communities%20of%20color%20because%20of%20a%20legacy%20of%20segregation%20and%20diminishing%20access%20to%20public%20facilities.%20While%20the%20lack%20of%20qualified%20lifeguards%20may%20partly%20stem%20from%20this%20problem%2C%20getting%20more%20lifeguards%20on%20stands%20could%20turn%20things%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussell%20has%20some%20ideas.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20labor%20academic%2C%20I%20tend%20to%20think%20that%20paying%20more%20money%20helps%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BEmployers%20lament%2C%20'Nobody%20wants%20to%20work.'%20But%20there%20is%20a%20solution%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-shortage-solution-pay-workers-higher-wages-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPay%20more%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20In%20fact%2C%20wage%20bumps%20have%20already%20helped%20curb%20lifeguard%20shortages%20in%20several%20US%20cities%2C%20including%20Chicago%2C%20Denver%2C%20Baltimore%2C%20and%20San%20Antonio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20enter%20our%20fourth%20year%20without%20enough%20lifeguards%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20them%20retaking%20the%20podium%20as%20the%20cultural%20idol%20of%20American%20summer.%20Even%20Hollywood's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaywatch-review-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2017%20%26quot%3BBaywatch%26quot%3B%20revival%20film%3C%2Fa%3E%20couldn't%20respark%20a%20love%20affair%20with%20the%20red%20suit.%20But%20while%20times%20and%20tastes%20may%20change%2C%20the%20attributes%20that%20make%20a%20summer%20job%20worthwhile%20stay%20more%20or%20less%20the%20same.%20When%20more%20cities%20prioritize%20safe%20water%20access%20for%20the%20masses%20%E2%80%94%20and%20pay%20lifeguards%20accordingly%20%E2%80%94%20the%20mighty%20lifeguard%20just%20may%20rise%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelli-maria-korducki%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EKelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20whose%20work%20focuses%20on%20work%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20culture.%20She's%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flifeguard-shortages-jobs-american-pools-beaches-closed-swimming-lessons-baywatch-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719999782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c60ddd1c84a0eaca80e44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flifeguard-shortages-jobs-american-pools-beaches-closed-swimming-lessons-baywatch-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pools%20across%20the%20country%20have%20been%20closed%20for%20years.%20It's%20the%20end%20of%20an%20American%20pastime.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flifeguard-shortages-jobs-american-pools-beaches-closed-swimming-lessons-baywatch-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Biden%20is%20isolated%20and%20insulated%20by%20a%20team%20of%20top%20aides%20who%20strictly%20control%20the%20advice%20he's%20given%2C%20per%20Politico%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Joe%20Biden%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6684f89c1f0c1cd6d73118da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22587%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3Cp%3EScott%20Olson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESources%20close%