g%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22My%20dad%20is%20Steve%20Ballmer.%20I%20spent%205%20years%20working%20as%20a%20product%20manager%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20before%20becoming%20a%20comedian.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6684647f268f62ba18a6e9a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPete%20Ballmer%2C%20Alisa%20Solo%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Abanti%20Chowdhury%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-ballmer-son-pete-net-worth-generational-wealth-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E29-year-old%20Pete%20Ballmer%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20standup%20comedian%20and%20former%20product%20manager%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20one%20of%20the%20sons%20of%20billionaire%20and%20former%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Steve%20Ballmer.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20kid%2C%20I%20liked%20computers.%20I%20used%20to%20subscribe%20to%20PCWorld%20Magazine%20because%20I%20liked%20reading%20about%20new%20products.%20I%20took%20computer%20science%20classes%20at%20my%20high%20school%20and%20really%20enjoyed%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20majored%20in%20computer%20science%20with%20a%20concentration%20in%20human-computer%20interaction%20at%20Stanford.%20Many%20people%20told%20me%20I%20was%20doing%20what%20my%20dad%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-ballmer-bill-gates-microsoft-billionaires-net-worth-microsoft-stock-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Ballmer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20did%2C%20but%20he%20wasn't%20a%20programmer.%20He%20was%20a%20business%20guy%20familiar%20with%20the%20subject%20but%20didn't%20push%20me%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20always%20told%20my%20brothers%20and%20me%20that%20he%20just%20wanted%20us%20to%20do%20what%20we%20were%20passionate%20about.%20He%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20he%20didn't%20have%20specific%20expectations%20for%20our%20achievements%2C%20but%20he%20did%20harp%20a%20lot%20on%20working%20hard%20and%20doing%20our%20best.%20He%20would%20always%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20going%20to%20do%20a%20job%2C%20do%20a%20job.%20And%20if%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20do%20a%20job%2C%20don't%20do%20a%20job.%26quot%3B%20The%20rhetoric%20was%2C%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20do%20something%2C%20do%20it%20to%20the%20fullest%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20worked%20a%20few%20internships%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20summers%20after%20my%20junior%20and%20senior%20years%20of%20high%20school%2C%20I%20did%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-software-engineering-internship-what-it-was-like-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineering%20internship%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20small%20startup%20called%20Dashwire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20then%20did%20a%20software%20engineering%20internship%20at%20Expedia%20the%20summer%20after%20my%20first%20year%20of%20college.%20I%20kind%20of%20hated%20it.%20I%20was%20fine%20as%20a%20programmer%20but%20wasn't%20the%20best%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20that%20I%20didn't%20love%20programming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20sophomore%20year%2C%20I%20heard%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpete-steve-ballmer-friendships-dating-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20my%20friends%3C%2Fa%3E%20talk%20about%20his%20product%20management%20internship.%20The%20nature%20of%20the%20role%20appealed%20to%20me%3B%20it's%20a%20people-oriented%20job%20while%20still%20being%20analytical%20and%20creative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20summer%2C%20I%20got%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-job-canva-product-manager-self-employed-financial-freedom-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproduct%20managemen