2_blank%5C%22%3Eradioactive%20water%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20disaster.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20rhetoric%20was%20stoked%20again%20on%20June%2024%20when%20a%20knife-wielding%20man%20in%20Suzhou%20attacked%20a%20Japanese%20woman%20and%20her%20son%20at%20a%20school%20bus%20stop%2C%20injuring%20the%20pair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20the%20third%20victim%20who%20seized%20the%20country's%20attention.%20School%20bus%20attendant%20Hu%20Youping%2C%20a%2055-year-old%20Chinese%20woman%2C%20rushed%20to%20protect%20the%20two%20foreigners%2C%20suffering%20stab%20wounds%20herself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20died%20later%20while%20receiving%20medical%20care%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgonganju.suzhou.gov.cn%2Fgaj%2Fgggs%2F202406%2Fb10b5b52abf944bbbe5da0f48f49ab2b.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolice%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20identified%20the%20suspect%20as%20an%20unemployed%2052-year-old%20man%20with%20the%20surname%20Zhou%2C%20saying%20he'd%20only%20recently%20arrived%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20whirlwind%20of%20emotion%20and%20debate%20ensued%20on%20social%20media.%20Hu%20was%20lauded%20as%20a%20hero%20%E2%80%94%20with%20some%20clamoring%20for%20the%20bus%20stop%20to%20be%20named%20after%20her%20%E2%80%94%20while%20anti-Japan%20hate%20speech%20swelled%20in%20posts%20and%20comments%20implying%20the%20attack%20was%20warranted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20two%20narratives%20intertwined%2C%20Chinese%20social%20media%20companies%20intervened%20in%20lockstep.%20It%20was%20clear%20the%20extremism%20had%20gone%20too%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20giant%20Tencent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnew.qq.com%2Frain%2Fa%2F20240629A07Y1D00%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Saturday%20condemning%20the%20hate%20speech%20and%20said%20it%20would%20crack%20down%20on%20posts%20related%20to%20the%20Suzhou%20stabbing%20that%20%26quot%3Bprovoke%20extreme%20nationalism.%26quot%3B%20Tencent%20runs%20WeChat%2C%20a%20super%20app%20that%20performs%20functions%20similar%20to%20WhatsApp%20and%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetEase%2C%20a%20major%20gaming%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.163.com%2Fdy%2Farticle%2FJ5SC406S051487S2.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20similar%20announcement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20it%20observed%20posts%20calling%20for%20%26quot%3Bresisting%20Japan%20and%20exterminating%20traitors%26quot%3B%20and%20accusing%20Hu%20of%20being%20a%20Japanese%20spy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.toutiao.com%2Fw%2F1803214247310336%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDouyin%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2F1934183965%2FOkPR1lEPA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWeibo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20China's%20versions%20of%20TikTok%20and%20Twitter%2C%20publicly%20slammed%20accounts%20that%20they%20said%20%26quot%3Bpromote%20extreme%20xenophobia%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bcheered%20for%20criminal%20behavior%20in%20the%20name%20of%20patriotism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20platforms%20said%20they%20took%20down%20thousands%20of%20posts%20and%20removed%20several%20dozen%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be0339db-22c4-48a0-82ae-a6e8a2800701%5C%22%3EChina's%20uneasy%20balance%20with%20Japan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20rare%20rebuke%20of%20nationalism%20on%20these%20platforms%2C%20a%20hotbed%20for%20inflammatory%20posts%20like%20the%202022%20calls%20to%20shoot%20down%20then-House%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi's%20plane%20when%20she%20visited%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20China's%20social%20media%20is%20heavily%20moderated%2C%20anti-Japanese%20rhetoric%20has%20been%20one%20of%20several%20popular%20nationalistic%20sentiments%20allowed%20to%20flourish%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20main%20hashtag%20for%20posts%20about%20the%20Japanese%20victims%20of%20the%20June%20knife%20attack%20was%20censored.%20However%2C%20discussion%20of%20Hu's%20death%20and%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgonganju.suzhou.gov.cn%2Fgaj%2Fgggs%2F202406%2Fb10b5b52abf944bbbe5da0f48f49ab2b.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eposthumous%20recognition%20for%20bravery%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20still%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recognition%20of%20Hu's%20actions%2C%20Japan's%20embassy%20in%20China%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2F1938487875%2FOl3qFrTBd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflew%20its%20national%20flag%20at%20half-mast.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20China's%20central%20government%20was%20directly%20involved%20in%20the%20crackdown.%20But%20social%20media%20firms%20in%20the%20country%20react%20sensitively%20to%20what%20the%20state%20deems%20acceptable%2C%20often%20simultaneously%20issuing%20announcements%20about%20undesirable%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20Cyberspace%20Administration%20tasks%20social%20media%20platforms%20with%20self-regulating%20content%20and%2C%20on%20June%2014%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cac.gov.cn%2F2024-06%2F14%2Fc_1720043894161555.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20set%20of%20rules%20%3C%2Fa%3Edetailing%20how%20internet%20providers%20should%20censor%20violent%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20anti-Japanese%20rhetoric%20also%20comes%20at%20an%20inconvenient%20time%20for%20Chinese%20officials%20hoping%20to%20bring%20in%20more%20business%20from%20Tokyo%20as%20the%20local%20economy%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuzhou%2C%20in%20eastern%20China's%20Jiangsu%20province%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20largest%20hubs%20for%20Japanese%20investment%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fregional.chinadaily.com.cn%2FSuzhouNewDistrict%2F2022-07%2F27%2Fc_792868.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethousands%20of%20Japanese%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.ifeng.com%2Fc%2F8asx18ggwqv%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20